column5: I can almost taste the poutine already!!! (And fresh Walleye)
Good Luck! Can't wait to hear how you did!

Two more days to go for us this week. So far it has been a pretty outstanding week of walleye fishing. We haven't caught any real monsters but we have consistently been throwing back walleyes that are over the 18¬î limit. We have multiple 25¬î walleye in our group with a lot more 23¬î-24¬î as well. The walleye all seem to still be pretty shallow. Water temps are 66-67 degrees in most areas of the lake. There have been multiple fish over 30¬î caught in camp this week with the biggest being 33¬î. Two more days to try and get my 30 incher! ü§ûüèª
Greetings, Team Walleye: Way to go!!! I was wondering as to how you were doing. The wife and I depart in about one hour. Good fishing and tight lines!!
Should be seeing the "hatch" by now. I hope you get a mayfly gorged Walleye over 30 inches!!! Chuck
Probably really close to the hatch in the lake. We were up in the Ord today and saw some flys on the surface. Haven't seen any yet in the lake. I'm assuming by this weekend there will be.
Thanks for the report. Later, Jay
Sure hope he posts a picture of a Walleye above 30 inches!! Heading up next Friday, can't wait!!! Chuck

Well we left all the 30 in here for everyone else To hopefully catch. It was a really good week of fishing however. Many fish over 20¬î each day. Fishing got a little tougher Thursday and today due to the sun and heat. Fish will definitely be moving deeper in the coming days. Another great trip in the books. I will post some pictures when I get home if I can figure out how to do it.
